reviewText:
Trine 3 was not as good as Trine 2, but not worse than Trine.

Pros:
The graphics and soundtrack are amazing. You would think a full 3D game would hinder the background graphic quality in comparison with its 2D predecessors, but that does not happen;
The story has more depth, and expands into things the previous games seemed to ignore completely and left me curious about;
The puzzles are more complex, if not actually harder. At least I had more to do than blow this up" or "jump this high" and that's a win for me;
There are now side stages where you are in control of only one character. Great for practicing the abilities that had to be retooled for 3D
